{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637891"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:46:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:46:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17677"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17677"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.75,0.13,0.03,0.09,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10391"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78238"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10391","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10391"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17677"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63647"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"10500"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24279"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24311"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78238","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78238"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe renin-angiotensin-aldosterone system plays a crucial role in blood pressure regulation. Angiotensin II is a key hormone in this pathway that acts on multiple target tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary physiological action of angiotensin II?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Causes systemic vasoconstriction","Inhibits sympathetic nerve activity","Decreases aldosterone secretion","Promotes sodium excretion","Reduces cardiac contractility"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESystemic vasoconstriction\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary physiological action of angiotensin II. By constricting arterioles throughout the body, it increases peripheral vascular resistance and raises blood pressure. Angiotensin II also stimulates aldosterone secretion, leading to sodium and water retention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAngiotensin II actually enhances sympathetic activity, so it does not \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibit sympathetic nerve activity\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ERather than \u003Cstrong\u003Edecreasing aldosterone secretion\u003C/strong\u003E, angiotensin II stimulates the adrenal cortex to release more aldosterone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EInstead of \u003Cstrong\u003Epromoting sodium excretion\u003C/strong\u003E, angiotensin II causes sodium retention through its effects on aldosterone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAngiotensin II has positive inotropic effects rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Ereducing cardiac contractility\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese combined actions of vasoconstriction and volume retention make angiotensin II a powerful regulator of blood pressure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Angiotensin II is a potent vasoconstrictor that increases systemic blood pressure.","Angiotensin II stimulates aldosterone secretion which promotes sodium and water retention.","Angiotensin II helps maintain blood pressure through both direct vascular effects and indirect renal effects."],"references":["Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Tortora, G. J., Mellifont, R., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Peoples, G., D, D. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, Asia-Pacific Edition,  2nd Edition. John Wiley \u0026 Sons Australia; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63647"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17677"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63647"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T22:43:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T22:44:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10391"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78238"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4933"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urinary","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"t